rossed%20out%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F689b8f73a17a8c5b4052bcd8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%C2%A0%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDepending%20on%20who%20you%20ask%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-young-kids-families-fleeing-big-cities-urban-doom-loop-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esuburban%20living%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20either%20the%20stuff%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-dream-shrinking-smaller-homes-fewer-kids-vacation-time-commutes-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAmerican%20dream%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20desolate%2C%20alienating%20existence%2C%20or%20something%20in%20between.%20But%20there%20is%20no%20doubt%20of%20the%20grip%20that%20the%20white%20picket%20fences%20and%20green%20lawns%20have%20on%20the%20American%20imagination.%20In%20his%201985%20book%20%3Cem%3ECrabgrass%20Frontier%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20historian%20Kenneth%20T.%20Jackson%20%E2%80%94%20perhaps%20the%20dean%20of%20American%20suburban%20studies%20%E2%80%94%20wrote%20that%20%26quot%3Bsuburbia%20has%20become%20the%20quintessential%20physical%20achievement%20of%20the%20United%20States%3B%20it%20is%20perhaps%20more%20representative%20of%20its%20culture%20than%20big%20cars%2C%20tall%20buildings%2C%20or%20professional%20football.%26quot%3B%20To%20many%20urbanists%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-priced-out-of-cities-into-suburbs-housing-crisis-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20suburbs%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20represent%20something%20a%20little%20more%20prosaic%2C%20though%20no%20less%20important%3A%20a%20major%20governance%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20particular%2C%20the%20suburbs%20pose%20a%20problem%20called%20municipal%20fragmentation.%20Most%20of%20the%20little%20bedroom%20communities%20surrounding%20a%20major%20city%20have%20their%20own%20governments%2C%20their%20own%20electorate%2C%20and%20their%20own%20set%20of%20policy%20priorities.%20The%20central%20problems%20of%20urban%20governance%20%E2%80%94%20how%20to%20run%20a%20safe%20and%20efficient%20transportation%20network%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnational-zoning-map-home-prices-down-real-estate-new-houses-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewhere%20to%20put%20housing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20how%20to%20cultivate%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-unemployed-dream-jobs-hiring-college-degree-graduation-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estrong%20job%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20are%20essentially%20regional%2C%20but%20the%20mosaics%20of%20incorporated%20towns%20and%20unincorporated%20county%20lands%20that%20surround%20major%20American%20cities%20struggle%20to%20properly%20coordinate%20to%20address%20these%20issues.%20Each%20little%20fiefdom%20is%20largely%20free%20to%20pursue%20its%20own%20goals%2C%20even%20if%20those%20goals%20conflict%20with%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20larger%20metropolitan%20region%2C%20and%20there%20are%20few%20regional%20bodies%20in%20the%20United%20States%20that%20have%20the%20muscle%20to%20overcome%20this%20parochialism.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20overcoming%20local%20parochialism%20is%20the%20key%20to%20creating%20vibrant%2C%20growing%20cities%20across%20the%20nation.%20If%20we're%20going%20to%20solve%20the%20housing%20crisis%2C%20build%20a%20transportation%20network%20that%20works%20for%20all%20people%2C%20and%20provide%20economic%20opportunity%20to%20all%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcss.umich.edu%2Fpublications%2Ffactsheets%2Fbuilt-environment%2Fus-cities-factsheet%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20than%2080%25%20of%20Americans%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20live%20in%20urban%20areas%2C%20then%20we%20need%20institutions%20that%20can%20tie%20together%20the%20towns%2C%20hamlets%2C%20and%20satellite%20cities%20of%20our%20major%20metropolitan%20regions%2C%20so%20that%20they%20all%20start%20moving%20in%20the%20same%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20understand%20the%20problem%20of%20municipal%20fragmentation%2C%20consider%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-manhattan-real-estate-housing-affordability-no-new-homes-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20City's%20housing%20shortage%3C%2Fa%3E.%20(By%20one%20estimate%2C%20the%20New%20York%20metropolitan%20area%20would%20need%20to%20build%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcbcny.org%2Fbuilding-crisis%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehalf%20a%20million%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20order%20to%20close%20the%20housing%20gap.)%20The%20city%20can%20and%20should%20stimulate%20a%20lot%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-legalization-tiny-backyard-homes-basements-adus-restricted-by-regulations-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emore%20housing%20production%3C%2Fa%3E%20within%20its%20borders%20(and%20is%20attempting%20to%20do%20so)%2C%20but%20even%20if%20the%20city%20council%20abolished%20all%20zoning%20laws%20tomorrow%20and%20allowed%20massive%20amounts%20of%20new%20construction%2C%20New%20York%20would%20probably%20still%20be%20digging%20out%20of%20a%20housing%20shortage%20in%20a%20decade%2C%20albeit%20a%20less%20severe%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20in%20part%20because%20New%20York%20City%20comprises%20less%20than%2010%25%20of%20the%20entire%20New%20York%20City%20metropolitan%20area%20in%20terms%20of%20surface%20area.%20The%20region%20as%20a%20whole%20includes%20more%20than%20900%20other%20municipalities%2C%20from%20New%20Haven%2C%20Connecticut%2C%20in%20the%20north%20to%20the%20seaside%20towns%20of%20southern%20New%20Jersey.%20Quite%20a%20few%20of%20those%20localities%20are%20affluent%20bedroom%20communities%20that%20have%20grown%20prosperous%20off%20their%20proximity%20to%20New%20York%20while%20providing%20the%20city%20with%20very%20little%20in%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20many%20residents%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fliving-in-greenwich-connecticut-houses-cars-wall-street-photos-2019-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGreenwich%2C%20Connecticut%3C%2Fa%3E%20(average%20household%20income%3A%20%24272%2C636)%20have%20lucrative%20jobs%20in%20Manhattan.%20They%20benefit%20from%20the%20city's%20booming%20economy%2C%20as%20well%20as%20its%20high%20concentration%20of%20skilled%20workers%20and%20major%20employers%20in%20high-wage%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fseeing-polo-match-in-greenwich-connecticut-wealthiest-towns-in-us-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eindustries%20like%20finance%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20their%20property%20taxes%20don't%20go%20to%20New%20York.%20Instead%20of%20seeing%20itself%20as%20part%20of%20the%20broader%20NYC%20area%20and%20welcoming%20people%20who%20are%20looking%20to%20secure%20their%20economic%20future%20there%2C%20Greenwich%20has%20instituted%20a%20draconian%20zoning%20code%20that%20keeps%20people%20out%20and%20contributes%20to%20the%20region's%20housing%20supply%20crunch.%20(It%20doesn't%20help%20that%20the%20governor%20of%20Connecticut%20recently%20vetoed%20a%20bill%20intended%20to%20mitigate%20the%20state's%20housing%20shortage.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Greenwich%20and%20every%20other%20exclusionary%20suburb%20in%20the%20New%20York%20metro%20area%20loosened%20up%20their%20zoning%2C%20it%20would%20go%20a%20long%20way%20toward%20easing%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-city-real-estate-prices-housing-apartments-eric-adams-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecentral%20city's%20affordability%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There's%20plenty%20of%20room%20there%3B%20even%20increasing%20Greenwich's%20population%20density%20to%20make%20it%20on%20par%20with%20a%20denser%20midsize%20city%20like%20New%20Haven%20would%20mean%20growing%20its%20population%20by%20fivefold%2C%20adding%20more%20than%20250%2C000%20residents.%20More%20homebuilding%20in%20the%20suburbs%20would%20not%20only%20make%20the%20region%20as%20a%20whole%20more%20affordable%2C%20but%20it%20would%20also%20give%20more%20enterprising%20people%20a%20chance%20to%20move%20to%20the%20area%2C%20work%2C%20build%20businesses%2C%20and%20contribute%20to%20the%20shared%20prosperity%20of%20the%20region.%20But%20officials%20in%20New%20York%20City%20have%20no%20jurisdictional%20authority%20to%20push%20other%20towns%20to%20greenlight%20more%20housing.%20And%20since%20the%20potential%20benefits%20are%20so%20diffuse%2C%20Greenwich%20residents%20who%20oppose%20more%20development%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyimbys-winning-lower-house-prices-rents-build-more-homes-neighborhoods-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eaka%20NIMBYs%3C%2Fa%3E)%20have%20little%20clear%20incentive%20to%20be%20part%20of%20a%20region-wide%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20metropolitan%20areas%20have%20solved%20this%20collective%20action%20problem%20through%20municipal%20consolidation%3A%20New%20York%20City's%20borders%20stopped%20at%20the%20edge%20of%20the%20Island%20of%20Manhattan%20until%20it%20absorbed%20the%20Bronx%2C%20Queens%2C%20Brooklyn%2C%20and%20Staten%20Island%20between%201873%20and%201879.%20More%20recently%2C%20Louisville%2C%20Kentucky%2C%20merged%20with%20surrounding%20Jefferson%20County%20in%202003.%20But%20in%20general%2C%20consolidation%20is%20a%20nineteenth-century%20phenomenon.%20Fragmentation%20is%20the%20norm%20in%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20unlikely%20that%20big%20cities%20will%20be%20able%20to%20annex%20surrounding%20counties%20en%20masse%20anytime%20soon%2C%20there%20is%20another%20way%20to%20fight%20municipal%20fragmentation%20and%20to%20alleviate%20the%20housing%20crunch%20on%20a%20wider%20scale%3A%20through%20regional%20super-governments%20that%20conduct%20planning%20and%20exercise%20some%20land%20use%20authority%20over%20entire%20metropolitan%20areas.%20The%20United%20States%20is%20already%20dotted%20with%20regional%20government%20authorities%20%E2%80%94%20in%20particular%2C%20the%20metropolitan%20planning%20organizations%20that%20help%20distribute%20federal%20transportation%20funding%2C%20like%20the%20New%20York%20Metropolitan%20Transportation%20Council%2C%20the%20San%20Francisco%20Bay%20Area's%20Metropolitan%20Transportation%20Commission%2C%20and%20the%20Chicago%20Metropolitan%20Agency%20for%20Planning.%20But%20regional%20bodies%20often%20have%20little%20power%20compared%20to%20cities%2C%20making%20the%20battle%20for%20change%20an%20uphill%20fight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20tradition%20of%20strong%20hyperlocal%20rule%20and%20weak%20regional%20government%20is%20fairly%20unusual%20across%20the%20globe.%20The%20regional%20governments%20of%20Barcelona%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhelsinki-skinny-home-can-fit-inside-a-parking-space-2017-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EHelsinki's%20urban%20areas%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20example%2C%20do%20genuine%20regional%20planning.%20And%20in%20stark%20contrast%20to%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Japan%20is%20subdivided%20into%20prefectures%2C%20which%20are%20supercharged%20regional%20governments%20that%20have%20broad%20control%20over%20planning%20and%20land%20use.%20That%20may%20help%20to%20explain%20why%20housing%20costs%20in%20big%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-build-like-tokyo-housing-crisis-doom-loop-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJapanese%20cities%20like%20Tokyo%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20largely%20remained%20stable%20even%20as%20the%20country's%20rural%20population%20has%20shrunk%20and%20its%20urban%20population%20has%20grown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20decades%20ago%2C%20California%20very%20nearly%20became%20the%20first%20US%20state%20to%20inch%20in%20Japan's%20direction.%20In%20some%20ways%2C%20the%20state%20is%20an%20ideal%20testing%20ground%20for%20super-regionalism%2C%20thanks%20to%20the%20extreme%20fragmentation%20of%20its%20largest%20metropolitan%20areas%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flos-angeles-wildfires-fireproof-my-home-roofs-siding-building-code-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGreater%20Los%20Angeles%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsan-francisco-doom-loop-fix-american-city-housing-transit-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESan%20Francisco%20Bay%20Area%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20its%20history%20of%20progressive%20experimentation%2C%20and%20its%20yawning%20housing%20shortage.%20Policymakers%20in%20the%20state%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20in%20the%20late%201980s%20and%20early%201990s%20thinking%20about%20solutions%20to%20municipal%20fragmentation.%20Some%20of%20what%20they%20came%20up%20with%20was%20genuinely%20radical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20Los%20Angeles%202000%20Committee%2C%20which%20then-Mayor%20Tom%20Bradley%20assembled%20to%20consider%20the%20city's%20future%20planning%20needs%2C%20issued%20a%20report%20in%201988%20that%20proposed%20a%20regional%20Growth%20Management%20Agency%20for%20greater%20Los%20Angeles.%20The%20goal%20of%20this%20agency%20would%20be%20to%20produce%20plans%20that%20would%20help%20the%20Los%20Angeles%20metro%20area%2C%20which%20sprawls%20over%204%2C850%20square%20miles%20and%20more%20than%20100%20municipalities%2C%20%26quot%3Bachieve%20a%20favorable%20balance%20between%20jobs%20and%20housing.%26quot%3B%20The%20agency%20would%20have%20been%20empowered%20to%2C%20for%20example%2C%20stimulate%20job%20growth%20in%20eastern%20Los%20Angeles%20and%20encourage%20greater%20housing%20production%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftarek-el-moussa-says-he-cant-make-money-on-california-starter-homes-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eprosperous%20Orange%20County%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInspired%20in%20part%20by%20the%20work%20of%20the%20Los%20Angeles%202000%20Committee%2C%20in%201989%20some%20influential%20Northern%20California%20residents%20secured%20both%20public%20and%20private%20funding%20to%20create%20the%20Bay%20Area%202020%20Commission.%20This%20commission's%20work%20was%20much%20more%20explicitly%20regionalist%2C%20and%20so%20its%20core%20recommendation%20was%20for%20a%20significantly%20more%20muscular%20regional%20planning%20mechanism%20than%20even%20the%20Los%20Angeles%20committee%20had%20devised.%20The%20Bay%20Area's%20commission%20proposed%20merging%20the%20area's%20three%20major%20regional%20bodies%20(the%20Association%20of%20Bay%20Area%20Governments%2C%20the%20Metropolitan%20Transportation%20Commission%2C%20and%20the%20Bay%20Area%20Air%20Quality%20Management%20District)%20into%20a%20single%20commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20Regional%20Commission%20would%20have%20had%20extensive%20powers%2C%20including%20the%20ability%20to%20levy%20fines%20on%20local%20governments%20that%20didn't%20comply%20with%20regional%20plans%2C%20and%20to%20issue%20permits%20for%20a%20proposed%20development%20anywhere%20in%20the%20Bay%20Area's%20nine%20counties.%20A%20bill%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%20state%20senate%20to%20implement%20Bay%20Vision%202020%2C%20but%2C%20needless%20to%20say%2C%20it%20didn't%20pass.%20Many%20local%20governments%2C%20and%20two%20of%20the%20three%20regional%20bodies%20that%20were%20supposed%20to%20merge%2C%20were%20not%20pleased%20with%20the%20prospect%20of%20ceding%20their%20autonomy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20wasn't%20even%20the%20spiciest%20proposal%20from%20the%20era.%20That%20honor%20belongs%20to%20an%20idea%20cooked%20up%20by%20then-Assembly%20Speaker%20Willie%20Brown.%20Brown%20was%20one%20of%20the%20central%20figures%20of%20late%2020th-century%20California%20politics%3A%20the%20first%20Black%20speaker%20of%20the%20Assembly%2C%20the%20first%20Black%20mayor%20of%20San%20Francisco%2C%20and%20the%20kingmaker%20who%20helped%20launch%20the%20political%20careers%20of%20both%20Kamala%20Harris%20and%20Gavin%20Newsom.%20He%20actually%20floated%20two%20separate%20proposals%20for%20overhauling%20regional%20government%20across%20the%20state.%20The%20first%20one%20was%20about%20as%20audacious%20as%20it%20gets%3A%20In%201987%2C%20Brown%20casually%20suggested%20completely%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Farchives%2Fla-xpm-1987-10-25-mn-16423-story.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabolishing%20city%20and%20county%20government%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20state%20of%20California%20and%20replacing%20it%20with%20a%20series%20of%20regional%20governments.%20In%20essence%2C%20he%20was%20proposing%20that%20California%20adopt%20the%20Japanese%20prefectural%20system.%20Though%20his%20idea%20never%20made%20it%20into%20legislative%20language%2C%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20later%2C%20he%20proposed%20something%20a%20little%20less%20radical.%20As%20Bill%20Fulton%2C%20the%20dean%20of%20California%20urban%20planners%2C%20wrote%20of%20Brown's%20proposal%20in%20his%20book%20about%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Reluctant%20Metropolis%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3EBrown's%20proposed%20%26quot%3BRegional%20Development%20and%20Infrastructure%20Agencies%26quot%3B%20would%20have%20been%20directly-elected%20boards%20that%20could%20pass%20%26quot%3Bjudgment%20on%20large%20development%20projects%20that%20were%20previously%20the%20province%20of%20local%20cities%20and%20counties.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20making%20the%20boards%20directly%20elected%2C%20these%20%26quot%3Bregional%20legislatures%26quot%3B%20would%20have%20seriously%20diluted%20the%20power%20of%20the%20NIMBY%20bedroom%20communities%20and%20drawn%20in%20ambitious%20politicians%20seeking%20to%20enact%20major%20projects%20on%20a%20region-wide%20scale.%20Once%20again%2C%20this%20proposal%20died%20on%20the%20vine%3A%20Brown%20didn't%20push%20it%20particularly%20hard%2C%20the%20governor%20wasn't%20interested%2C%20and%20a%20looming%20recession%20bumped%20regionalism%20off%20the%20legislative%20agenda.%20But%20maybe%20it's%20time%20to%20take%20another%20look%20at%20some%20of%20these%20ideas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20states%20like%20California%20did%20beef%20up%20their%20regional%20governments%2C%20it%20could%20go%20a%20long%20way%20toward%20solving%20the%20housing%20crisis.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcayimby.org%2Freports%2Fhousing-underproduction-in-california%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2023%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20California%20YIMBY%20(my%20former%20employer%2C%20full%20disclosure)%20found%20indications%20that%20the%20biggest%20potential%20housing%20gains%20from%20zoning%20and%20land%20use%20reforms%20can%20be%20found%20in%20suburbs%2C%20not%20the%20high-cost%20cities%20they%20surround.%20Eliminating%20zoning%20in%20San%20Francisco%20could%20yield%20a%20lot%20more%20units%2C%20but%20doing%20the%20same%20in%20Marin%20County%20would%20lead%20to%20much%20bigger%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGranted%2C%20implementing%20something%20like%20Brown's%20proposal%20for%20regional%20super-governments%20would%20likely%20infuriate%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20in%20both%20San%20Francisco%20%3Cem%3Eand%20%3C%2Fem%3EMarin.%20Opponents%20would%20no%20doubt%20describe%20regionalism%20as%20an%20unconscionable%20usurpation%20of%20local%20democracy.%20In%20return%2C%20I%20would%20argue%20that%20region-wide%20planning%20is%20%3Cem%3Emore%3C%2Fem%3E%20democratic%20than%20giving%20exclusive%20enclaves%20like%20Sausalito%20free%20rein%20to%20write%20their%20own%20rules%20and%20lock%20out%20lower-income%20residents%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20region.%20If%20hyper-local%20control%20is%20what%20got%20us%20the%20Bay%20Area's%20current%20housing%20and%20homelessness%20crisis%2C%20what%20is%20it%20really%20worth%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20may%20never%20get%20the%20Bay%20Area%20mega-city%20that%20Willie%20Brown%20seems%20to%20have%20envisioned.%20But%20at%20a%20time%20when%20many%20Americans%20are%20concerned%20about%20housing%20costs%20and%20commute%20times%2C%20even%20some%20halfway%