ion.%20A%20range%20officer%20that%20used%20to%20work%20here%20gifted%20me%20a%20camera%20in%202002%20and%20I%E2%80%99ve%20been%20taking%20photos%20ever%20since.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20keep%20any%20of%20the%20pictures%2C%20I%20submit%20them%20all%20to%20the%20forest%20office%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EEncounters%20With%20The%20Wild%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhenever%20I%20take%20tourists%20and%20researchers%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F318674%2Fkerala-teacher-grows-mini-miyawaki-forest-herbal-garden-on-school-campus%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20into%20the%20forest%20%3C%2Fa%3EI%20tell%20them%20a%20few%20simple%20things.%20If%20you%20spot%20an%20animal%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20get%20scared%20and%20don%E2%80%99t%20make%20noises%20or%20run.%20The%20key%20is%20to%20be%20silent.%20The%20second%20thing%20and%20the%20most%20important%20thing%20to%20remember%20is%20that%20this%20is%20the%20animals%20habitat%2C%20if%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20do%20anything%20to%20them%2C%20they%20won%E2%80%99t%20do%20anything%20to%20you%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20so%20many%20encounters%20that%20I%E2%80%99ve%20had%20with%20the%20wild%20animals.%20A%20few%20years%20back%2C%20I%20was%20guiding%20a%20few%20researchers%20through%20the%20forest%20and%20we%20spotted%20a%20lone%20elephant.%20Everyone%20hid%20behind%20trees%20on%20seeing%20the%20tusker.%20When%20the%20elephant%20heard%20our%20footsteps%2C%20I%20saw%20him%20reach%20out%20with%20his%20trunk%20to%20find%20us.%20But%20luckily%2C%20he%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20reach%20in%20completely%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says%2C%20relieved.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20Maari%2C%20the%20scariest%20encounter%20was%20with%20a%20wild%20tiger.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20alone%20that%20day%20and%20was%20trying%20to%20clear%20my%20path%20of%20the%20twigs%20and%20leaves%20in%20the%20forest.%20Suddenly%2C%20I%20looked%20up%20and%20right%20next%20to%20me%20stood%20a%20wild%20tiger%20staring%20right%20at%20me.%20Then%20for%20the%20next%2015%20minutes%2C%20both%20the%20tiger%20and%20I%20were%20imitating%20each%20other.%20When%20I%20sat%20down%20quietly%2C%20he%20also%20sat.%20When%20I%20got%20up%2C%20he%20also%20moved%20back.%20Then%20suddenly%2C%20when%20I%20made%20a%20loud%20noise%2C%20the%20tiger%20ran%20away.%20The%20next%20day%20when%20I%20came%20back%20to%20the%20same%20spot%2C%20I%20found%20the%20remains%20of%20a%20Sambar%20Deer%20lying%20there.%20That%E2%80%99s%20when%20I%20realised%20that%20I%20had%20encountered%20a%20hungry%20tiger%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeopards%2C%20bears%2C%20tigers%2C%20stray%20wolves%2C%20snakes%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20long%20list%20of%20animals%20that%20Maari%20has%20encountered.%20But%20rather%20than%20being%20scared%2C%20this%20man%20has%20embraced%20these%20experiences%20that%20have%20brought%20him%20closer%20to%20the%20wild.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESilent%20Valley%20Today%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FFeatured-Image-1-2020-04-01T123007.221.png%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FFeatured-Image-1-2020-04-01T123007.221.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FFeatured-Image-1-2020-04-01T123007.221-300x157.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FFeatured-Image-1-2020-04-01T123007.221-500x262.png%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2FFeatured-Image-1-2020-04-01T123007.221-768x402.png%20768w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-im