47%20Snow%20Leopards%20With%20Just%20a%20Blanket%20%26amp%3B%20Net%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20interviews%20and%20reporting%20for%20this%20story%20were%20conducted%20in%202020%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%20in%20Chilling%2C%20a%20small%20village%20approximately%2060%20km%20from%20Leh%2C%2042-year-old%20Khenrab%20Phuntsog%20would%20regularly%20spot%20snow%20leopards%20at%20a%20distance%20while%20taking%20out%20the%20household%20goats%20and%20sheep%20for%20grazing%20up%20on%20mountain%20pastures%20nearby.%20With%20Chilling%20situated%20inside%20the%20famous%20Hemis%20National%20Park%2C%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20hard%20to%20spot%20snow%20leopards%20if%20one%20climbed%20up%20to%20the%20higher%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20was%20during%20preparations%20for%20his%20grandmother%E2%80%99s%20cremation%2C%20when%20he%20was%20aged%2012%2C%20that%20he%20actually%20came%20within%20100%20metres%20of%20a%20snow%20leopard.%20It%20was%20a%20sight%20he%20would%20never%20forget.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%20wp-image-239903%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124727.524-1754570680.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124727.524-1754570680.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124727.524-1754570680-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124727.524-1754570680-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124727.524-1754570680-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124727.524-1754570680-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-483430%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EWildlife%20guards%20like%20Khenrab%20identify%20areas%20like%20ridgelines%2C%20broken%20cliffs%2C%20deep%20valleys%20and%20hanging%20rocks%20where%20snow%20leopards%20usually%20traverse%2C%20to%20install%20camera%20traps.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20had%20gone%20with%20two%20local%20painters%20for%20the%20finishing%20touches%20on%20the%20structure%20where%20my%20grandmother%20was%20to%20be%20cremated.%20While%20they%20were%20at%20work%2C%20one%20of%20the%20painters%20pointed%20towards%20the%20opposite%20mountain%20slope%20at%20the%20snow%20leopard%20quietly%20waiting%20just%20above%20a%20herd%20of%20blue%20sheep.%20Initially%2C%20the%20rest%20of%20us%20didn%E2%80%99t%20see%20it.%20But%20when%20it%20took%20a%20couple%20of%20long%20leaps%20down%2C%20we%20saw%20it.%20It%20had%20caught%20one%20of%20the%20sheep%20and%20went%20for%20the%20kill%2C%E2%80%9D%20recalled%20Khenrab%20in%20a%20conversation%20with%20The%20Better%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20that%20magnificent%20sighting%20that%20inspired%20Khenrab%20to%20first%20volunteer%20with%20the%20Wildlife%20Protection%20Department%2C%20and%20eventually%2C%20join%20it%20as%20a%20wildlife%20guard%20at%20the%20age%20of%2022%20in%20the%20year%202000.%20Since%20then%2C%20he%20has%20rescued%2047%20snow%20leopards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ETracking%20snow%20leopards%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20last%20scientific%20survey%20conducted%20through%20camera%20traps%20in%202012%2C%20the%20number%20of%20snow%20leopards%20in%20the%203%2C350%20sq%20km-large%20Hemis%20National%20Park%20stood%20at%2011%2C%20compared%20to%207%20in%202006.%20However%2C%20for%20those%20surveys%2C%20camera%20traps%20were%20only%20installed%20across%20300%20sq%20km.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20now%20in%20the%20process%20of%20completing%20another%20census%20for%20snow%20leopards%20using%20extensive%20camera%20trapping%20methods%20in%20different%20parts%20of%20%3Cstrong%3ELadakh%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20including%20in%20Changthang%2C%20Hemis%20National%20Park%2C%20Kargil%20and%20Nubra%20Valley.%20In%20Hemis%20National%20Park%2C%20we%20have%20about%2060%20snow%20leopards%20today.%20For%20this%20census%20camera%20traps%20were%20installed%20in%20half%20the%20total%20area%20unlike%20in%202006%20and%202012.%20If%20you%20take%20all%20of%20Ladakh%2C%20however%2C%20my%20guess%20is%20that%20the%20figure%20would%20be%20above%20250.%20This%20census%20is%20being%20carried%20out%20under%20the%20guidance%20of%20the%20Wildlife%20Institute%20of%20India.%20The%20results%20of%20this%20census%20may%20come%20by%20the%20end%20of%20this%20year%20or%20early%20next%20year%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWildlife%20guards%20like%20Khenrab%20identify%20areas%20like%20ridgelines%2C%20broken%20cliffs%2C%20deep%20valleys%20and%20hanging%20rocks%20where%20snow%20leopards%20usually%20traverse%2C%20to%20install%20camera%20traps.%20Rolling%20and%20flat%20land%20isn%E2%80%99t%20really%20conducive%20terrain%20for%20the%20snow%20leopard%2C%20although%20for%20this%20census%20camera%20traps%20have%20been%20installed%20in%20not%20so%20conducive%20terrain%20as%20well%2C%20to%20ensure%20that%20none%20are%20missed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%20wp-image-239894%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124833.987-1754569909.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22From%202000%20onwards%2C%20the%20introduction%20of%20ecotourism%2C%20particularly%20in%20areas%20like%20the%20Hemis%20National%20Park%2C%20played%20a%20big%20part%20in%20preventing%20the%20snow%20leopard%20killings%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124833.987-1754569909.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124833.987-1754569909-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124833.987-1754569909-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124833.987-1754569909-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124833.987-1754569909-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-483413%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EFrom%202000%20onwards%2C%20the%20introduction%20of%20ecotourism%2C%20particularly%20in%20areas%20like%20the%20Hemis%20National%20Park%2C%20played%20a%20big%20part%20in%20preventing%20the%20snow%20leopard%20killings%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKnowing%20where%20to%20install%20camera%20traps%20is%20a%20result%20of%20Khenrab%E2%80%99s%2020%20years%20of%20experience%20in%20tracking%20the%20elusive%20snow%20leopard.%20As%20a%20tracker%2C%20the%20first%20things%20he%20looks%20out%20for%20are%20indirect%20signs%20like%20pugmarks%2C%20scrapes%2C%20faeces%2C%20scent-sprays%2C%20claw-rakes%20and%20the%20remains%20from%20kills.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20best%20times%20to%20spot%20them%20are%20early%20morning%20and%20late%20evening.%20When%20looking%20for%20scrapes%20or%20faeces%2C%20you%20can%20find%20them%20in%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20valley%20or%20along%20the%20ridgeline.%20They%20make%20a%20pile%20of%20sand%20with%20their%20hind%20legs%20sitting%20on%20the%20ground%20and%20then%20urinate%20atop%20it.%20This%20is%20how%20they%20mark%20territory.%20They%20also%20rub%20their%20necks%20or%20cheeks%20on%20hanging%20rocks%2C%20leaving%20behind%20fur.%20One%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20look%20for%20high%20hanging%20rocks%20but%20suitably%20sized%20ones%2C%20where%20they%20can%20stand%20up%20and%20rub%20their%20necks.%20Here%20they%20also%20urinate%20and%20spray%20a%20pungent%20liquid%20from%20scent%20glands%20located%20under%20the%20base%20of%20the%20tail.%20Each%20one%20has%20its%20own%20unique%20scent%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Khenrab.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%20wp-image-239891%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124938.437-1754570099.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22During%20his%20two-decade%20tenure%20as%20a%20wildlife%20guard%2C%20Khenrab%20has%20been%20involved%20in%20rescuing%2047%20snow%20leopards.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124938.437-1754570099.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124938.437-1754570099-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124938.437-1754570099-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124938.437-1754570099-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F08%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-08-07T124938.437-1754570099-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-483421%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EDuring%20his%20two-decade%20tenure%20as%20a%20wildlife%20guard%2C%20Khenrab%20has%20been%20involved%20in%20rescuing%2047%20snow%20leopards.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20February-March%2C%20which%20is%20the%20mating%20season%20for%20the%20snow%20leopards%2C%20these%20hanging%20rocks%20are%20used%20frequently%20to%20scan%20and%20smell%20for%20potential%20mates.%20If%20these%20signs%20don%E2%80%99t%20work%2C%20they%20start%20calling%20each%20other%20on%20top%20of%20these%20ridgelines%20since%20this%20is%20the%20quickest%20way%20to%20communicate.%20Once%20you%20know%20where%20to%20look%2C%20the%20likelihood%20of%20spotting%20a%20snow%20leopard%20directly%20through%20your%20binoculars%20increases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ERescuing%20snow%20leopards%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20late%201970s%20and%2080s%2C%20some%20snow%20leopards%20were%20killed%20by%20the%20local%20populace%20in%20retaliation%20for%20their%20attacks%20on%20livestock.%20These%20predators%20would%20enter%20various%20corral%20pens%20in%20villages%20and%20kill%20livestock%2C%20a%20major%20source%20of%20income%20for%20many%20families.%20When%20snow%20leopards%20get%20sick%2C%20old%20or%20can%E2%80%99t%20hunt%20in%20the%20wild%2C%20they%20target%20livestock%20in%20corral%20pens%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20kills%20have%20significantly%20reduced%20since%20then%20because%20of%20awareness%20raised%20by%20the%20Wildlife%20Protection%20Department%20and%20other%20government%20agencies%20about%20the%20legal%20penalties%20involved%20for%20killing%20snow%20leopards%2C%20including%20jail%20time.%20Today%2C%20whenever%20a%20snow%20leopard%20enters%20a%20human%20habitation%2C%20the%20people%20immediately%20call%20the%20rescue%20team%20of%20the%20Wildlife%20Protection%20Department.%20After%20it%E2%80%99s%20in%20the%20safe%20hands%20of%20the%20rescue%20team%2C%20a%20vet%20assesses%20its%20medical%20condition.%20Once%20the%20snow%20leopard%20is%20deemed%20medically%20fit%2C%20it%20is%20let%20back%20into%20the%20wild.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%20wp-image-239905%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%20120